===[[Noun]]===
[[Plural]] '''polyhedrons''' or '''polyhedra'''

===[[Etymology]]===
New Latin, from Greek ''poly'' "many" + ''hedron'' "seat"; compare French ''[[polyèdre]]''

===[[Pronunciation]]===
IPA: /ˌpɒlɪ'hiːdrən/; plural /ˌpɒlɪ'hiːdrə/

#''(Geometry)'' a solid with many faces.
#''(Optics)'' a [[polyscope]], or multiplying glass.

